Overview
This module covered how to analyze Windows Event Logs to detect suspicious activity, reconstruct attacker timelines, and identify indicators of compromise. 
Windows Event Logs are one of the most valuable data sources available to a SOC analyst in a Windows-heavy environment.

Key Concepts Covered

Understanding the Windows Event Log structure and key log channels
Identifying high-value Event IDs for security investigations
Correlating logon events to detect lateral movement and privilege escalation
Detecting persistence mechanisms through scheduled tasks and service creation logs
Analyzing PowerShell and command-line execution logs for suspicious activity


