Key Takeaways
Windows Event Logs tell a detailed story when read in sequence. Logon Type values are particularly useful
Type 3 (network logon) and Type 10 (remote interactive) are common indicators of lateral movement.
PowerShell script block logging (Event ID 4104) is one of the most valuable sources of evidence when investigating post-exploitation activity,
as it captures the actual commands executed even when obfuscation is used.
